items.snippet:
In number theory, the general number field sieve (GNFS) is the most efficient 
classical algorithm known for factoring integers larger than 100 digits.

items.title: Quadratic sieve - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
The quadratic sieve algorithm (QS) is an integer factorization algorithm and, in 
practice, the second fastest method known (after the general number field sieve).
